AU  - Smith-Hanratty, Brendan
AU  - Walker, Ryan
JO  - Vascular Access
AB  - Ultrasound is commonly used to assist with peripheral vascular access and there is growing evidence that there is an advantage to using guidewires to aid insertion. This prospective observational study compares outcomes in ultrasound-guided peripheral cannulation using either standard catheter-over-needle devices or a single lumen arterial catheter inserted using the Seldinger technique. Analysis of results demonstrated a clear advantage in terms of device survival to completion of therapy in the guidewire group.
